    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You cloak yourself in a fey magic that makes others want to serve you. For up to 1 minute, you can cast <em>Command </em>as a bonus action.</p>\n<details>\n<summary style=\"padding-bottom:8px\"><strong>Full Description</strong></summary>\n<blockquote style=\"font-style:normal\">\n<p>As a bonus action, you cast @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-spells.UFyMGkLPBAGvdsvO]{Command}, without expending a spell slot, and you take on an appearance of unearthly beauty for 1 minute or until your <strong>concentration </strong>ends (as if you were concentrating on a spell). During this time, you can cast <em>Command</em> as a bonus action on each of your turns, without expending a spell slot.</p>\n<p>Any creature charmed by you automatically fails its saving throw against the <em>Command</em> you cast with this feature.</p>\n<p>Once you use this feature, you canâ€™t use it again until you finish a <strong>long rest</strong>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</details>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p><em>Note: After adding </em>@Compendium[5e-complete.5e-spells.UFyMGkLPBAGvdsvO]{Command}<em> to your character, set Preparation Mode to Innate with 1 use per Long Rest. You can also change the casting time to 1 Bonus Action.</em></p>\n</section>",
